"use strict";(globalThis.webpackChunkgithub_website=globalThis.webpackChunkgithub_website||[]).push([[130],{7735(e){e.exports=JSON.parse('{"archive":{"blogPosts":[{"id":"ai-powered-systems-production","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/ai-powered-systems-production","editUrl":"https://github.com/cyashu99/github-website/tree/main/blog/2026-02-09-ai-powered-systems/index.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-02-09-ai-powered-systems/index.md","title":"Productionizing AI-Powered Systems at Scale","description":"Integrating AI capabilities like GPT-4o into production systems presents unique challenges. In this post, I\'ll share insights from building an AI-powered dashboard summarization system that processes diverse data sources and delivers real-time insights.","date":"2026-02-09T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"ai","permalink":"/blog/tags/ai"},{"inline":true,"label":"machine-learning","permalink":"/blog/tags/machine-learning"},{"inline":true,"label":"distributed-systems","permalink":"/blog/tags/distributed-systems"},{"inline":true,"label":"production","permalink":"/blog/tags/production"}],"readingTime":1.5,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Yashika Chaudhary","title":"Senior Product Engineer at Sprinklr","url":"https://github.com/yashika-chaudhary1999","socials":{},"key":null,"page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"ai-powered-systems-production","title":"Productionizing AI-Powered Systems at Scale","authors":[{"name":"Yashika Chaudhary","title":"Senior Product Engineer at Sprinklr","url":"https://github.com/yashika-chaudhary1999"}],"tags":["ai","machine-learning","distributed-systems","production"],"date":"2026-02-09T00:00:00.000Z"},"unlisted":false,"nextItem":{"title":"Building Resilient Enterprise Integrations","permalink":"/blog/building-resilient-integrations"}},"content":"Integrating AI capabilities like GPT-4o into production systems presents unique challenges. In this post, I\'ll share insights from building an AI-powered dashboard summarization system that processes diverse data sources and delivers real-time insights.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## The Challenge\\n\\nBuilding AI-powered systems requires addressing:\\n\\n- **Latency**: AI API calls can be slow and unpredictable\\n- **Cost**: Managing API costs at scale\\n- **Reliability**: Handling API failures and rate limits\\n- **Data Quality**: Ensuring clean, preprocessed inputs\\n- **Scalability**: Processing high volumes efficiently\\n\\n## Architecture Approach\\n\\n### Distributed System Design\\n\\nThe system leverages distributed patterns:\\n\\n- **Microservices**: Separate services for data collection, preprocessing, and AI processing\\n- **Message Queues**: Kafka for reliable event processing\\n- **Caching**: Redis for frequently accessed data\\n- **Load Balancing**: Distributing requests across multiple instances\\n\\n### Data Pipeline\\n\\nA robust data pipeline ensures:\\n\\n1. **Collection**: Aggregating data from multiple sources\\n2. **Preprocessing**: Cleaning and normalizing data\\n3. **Enrichment**: Adding context and metadata\\n4. **AI Processing**: Sending to GPT-4o with proper error handling\\n5. **Delivery**: Caching and serving results efficiently\\n\\n### Reliability Patterns\\n\\n- **Retry Logic**: Exponential backoff for transient failures\\n- **Circuit Breakers**: Preventing cascade failures\\n- **Fallback Mechanisms**: Graceful degradation when AI is unavailable\\n- **Rate Limiting**: Managing API quotas effectively\\n\\n## Key Learnings\\n\\n1. **Caching is Essential**: Cache AI responses to reduce costs and latency\\n2. **Preprocessing Matters**: Clean, structured inputs improve AI output quality\\n3. **Monitor Everything**: Track latency, costs, and error rates\\n4. **Design for Failure**: AI APIs can fail; systems must handle it gracefully\\n\\n## Results\\n\\n- **Real-time Insights**: Delivered actionable dashboards in seconds\\n- **Cost Optimization**: Intelligent caching reduced API calls by 60%\\n- **High Reliability**: 99.9% uptime despite external API dependencies\\n- **Scalability**: Handled 10x traffic increase without issues\\n\\n---\\n\\n*Productionizing AI systems requires the same rigor as any distributed system: proper architecture, comprehensive monitoring, and designing for failure. The AI component is just one part of a larger, reliable system.*"},{"id":"building-resilient-integrations","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/building-resilient-integrations","editUrl":"https://github.com/cyashu99/github-website/tree/main/blog/2026-02-09-building-resilient-integrations/index.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-02-09-building-resilient-integrations/index.md","title":"Building Resilient Enterprise Integrations","description":"Building enterprise integrations that connect major CRM platforms like Salesforce, Zendesk, and Dynamics 365 requires careful attention to reliability, scalability, and fault tolerance. In this post, I\'ll share insights from designing and implementing resilient integration solutions.","date":"2026-02-09T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"microservices","permalink":"/blog/tags/microservices"},{"inline":true,"label":"integrations","permalink":"/blog/tags/integrations"},{"inline":true,"label":"architecture","permalink":"/blog/tags/architecture"},{"inline":true,"label":"resilience","permalink":"/blog/tags/resilience"}],"readingTime":1.41,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Yashika Chaudhary","title":"Senior Product Engineer at Sprinklr","url":"https://github.com/yashika-chaudhary1999","socials":{},"key":null,"page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"building-resilient-integrations","title":"Building Resilient Enterprise Integrations","authors":[{"name":"Yashika Chaudhary","title":"Senior Product Engineer at Sprinklr","url":"https://github.com/yashika-chaudhary1999"}],"tags":["microservices","integrations","architecture","resilience"],"date":"2026-02-09T00:00:00.000Z"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Productionizing AI-Powered Systems at Scale","permalink":"/blog/ai-powered-systems-production"},"nextItem":{"title":"Welcome to My Website","permalink":"/blog/welcome"}},"content":"Building enterprise integrations that connect major CRM platforms like Salesforce, Zendesk, and Dynamics 365 requires careful attention to reliability, scalability, and fault tolerance. In this post, I\'ll share insights from designing and implementing resilient integration solutions.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## The Challenge\\n\\nEnterprise integrations face unique challenges:\\n\\n- **High Volume**: Processing millions of events daily\\n- **SLA Requirements**: Ensuring 99.9%+ uptime\\n- **Fault Tolerance**: Handling failures gracefully without data loss\\n- **Real-time Sync**: Maintaining data consistency across platforms\\n\\n## Architecture Patterns\\n\\n### Event-Driven Architecture\\n\\nUsing Apache Kafka as the backbone for event-driven patterns provides:\\n\\n- **Decoupling**: Services communicate through events, not direct calls\\n- **Scalability**: Horizontal scaling of consumers\\n- **Reliability**: Message persistence and replay capabilities\\n- **Observability**: Built-in monitoring and tracing\\n\\n### gRPC for Inter-Service Communication\\n\\ngRPC offers several advantages over traditional REST:\\n\\n- **Performance**: HTTP/2 multiplexing and binary protocol\\n- **Type Safety**: Strong typing with Protocol Buffers\\n- **Streaming**: Bidirectional streaming for real-time updates\\n- **Efficiency**: Lower latency and bandwidth usage\\n\\n### Failure Notification Pipeline\\n\\nA Kafka-driven failure notification pipeline ensures:\\n\\n- **Visibility**: Real-time alerts for integration failures\\n- **Traceability**: Complete audit trail of events\\n- **Recovery**: Automatic retry mechanisms\\n- **Customer Transparency**: Status updates and error reporting\\n\\n## Key Learnings\\n\\n1. **Idempotency is Critical**: Design operations to be safely retryable\\n2. **Observability First**: Comprehensive logging, tracing, and metrics\\n3. **Graceful Degradation**: Systems should degrade gracefully under load\\n4. **Testing at Scale**: Load testing with production-like volumes\\n\\n## Results\\n\\n- **50% Resource Reduction**: Consolidated architecture reduced resource usage\\n- **80% Efficiency Improvement**: Payload diffing eliminated redundant processing\\n- **High Availability**: Multiple go-lives with zero downtime\\n- **Improved Developer Experience**: Faster onboarding and easier maintenance\\n\\n---\\n\\n*Building resilient integrations requires a combination of solid architecture patterns, comprehensive testing, and continuous monitoring. The key is designing for failure from the start.*"},{"id":"welcome","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/welcome","editUrl":"https://github.com/cyashu99/github-website/tree/main/blog/2026-02-09-welcome/index.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-02-09-welcome/index.md","title":"Welcome to My Website","description":"Welcome to my personal website!","date":"2026-02-09T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"welcome","permalink":"/blog/tags/welcome"},{"inline":true,"label":"introduction","permalink":"/blog/tags/introduction"},{"inline":true,"label":"software-engineering","permalink":"/blog/tags/software-engineering"}],"readingTime":0.89,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Yashika Chaudhary","title":"Senior Product Engineer at Sprinklr","url":"https://github.com/yashika-chaudhary1999","image_url":"https://github.com/yashika-chaudhary1999.png","imageURL":"https://github.com/yashika-chaudhary1999.png","socials":{},"key":null,"page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"welcome","title":"Welcome to My Website","authors":[{"name":"Yashika Chaudhary","title":"Senior Product Engineer at Sprinklr","url":"https://github.com/yashika-chaudhary1999","image_url":"https://github.com/yashika-chaudhary1999.png","imageURL":"https://github.com/yashika-chaudhary1999.png"}],"tags":["welcome","introduction","software-engineering"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Building Resilient Enterprise Integrations","permalink":"/blog/building-resilient-integrations"}},"content":"Welcome to my personal website!\\n\\nI\'m **Yashika Chaudhary**, a Senior Product Engineer specializing in Distributed Systems, currently working at Sprinklr. I\'m passionate about building scalable, resilient systems that power enterprise-level applications.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## What You\'ll Find Here\\n\\nThis website serves as a comprehensive portfolio of my work, experiences, and technical insights. You\'ll find:\\n\\n- **Professional Background**: My journey from IIT BHU to leading integration projects at Sprinklr\\n- **Technical Projects**: Deep dives into enterprise integrations, webhook architectures, and AI-powered systems\\n- **Skills & Expertise**: Detailed breakdown of my technical competencies\\n- **Blog Posts**: Articles on software engineering, system design, and best practices\\n\\n## My Focus Areas\\n\\n- **Distributed Systems**: Designing fault-tolerant microservices architectures\\n- **Enterprise Integrations**: Building seamless connections between major CRM platforms\\n- **Cloud Infrastructure**: Deploying scalable solutions on AWS with Kubernetes\\n- **AI/ML Applications**: Integrating AI capabilities into production systems\\n\\nFeel free to explore the documentation section to learn more about my work and projects. I\'m always open to connecting with fellow engineers and discussing interesting technical challenges!\\n\\n---\\n\\n*Stay tuned for more articles on distributed systems, microservices architecture, and software engineering best practices.*"}]}}')}}]);